    <abstract>
      <t>This document defines a new protocol element, an Internationalized Resource Identifier (IRI). An IRI is a sequence of characters from the Universal Character Set [10646]. A mapping from IRIs to URIs [RFC 2396] is defined, which means that IRIs can be used instead of URIs where appropriate to identify resources</t>
